<subSubSection id="4BF5A5B312CF11FD1BB0F4FB2D5DA1CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FC9E3E04407C28285627EC7AC2A929C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B4873E3C5965B56564E806AD99502F60" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: East Rhodopes, Meden buk vill., 03.07.2014, 1 w.; same place, 22.04.2021, 2 w., leg. ALG; Ograzhden Mt., Drakata vill., 09.09.2021, 10 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="895F9919075B1729A651F2DF4A8A3946" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0E5D22C3D10E37B882A6D93523E5DBA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="18659998612E87D2CB42C68F2A0A594A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB8B97F40455DD52A8AC4FE03E7BC018" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
This is a species from the 
<taxonomicName id="0D1F2E8E129753FC27393BBA67AD25E8" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus kiesenwetteri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiesenwetteri">
<emphasis id="D16DE1FCBAD3CFFCA4BDDD0F4BD82BE8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Camponotus kiesenwetteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, which occurs in Greece, Turkey, the Republic of North Macedonia and Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="5C8E981BC5F68780FB09231D383E6663" author="Salata, S." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="85 - 107" refId="B7725970" refString="Salata, S., Loss, A. C., Karaman, C., Kiran, K., Borowiec, L., 2019. Review of the Camponotus kiesenwetteri group (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) in the Aegean with the description of a new species. ZooKeys 899: 85 - 107" title="Review of the Camponotus kiesenwetteri group (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) in the Aegean with the description of a new species" volume="899" year="2019">Salata et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In Bulgaria, the species was reported in two localities: Struma Valley and South Pirin Mt. (
<bibRefCitation id="67DBD75027A41E103C50AB87859446C7" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Myrmecological News" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 3" refId="B7725822" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., 2011. First records of three ant species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Bulgaria. Myrmecological News 14: 1 - 3" title="First records of three ant species (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volume="14" year="2011">Lapeva-Gjonova 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
